{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting metadata and inheritance**\\n\\nI’m thinking about untracked metadata and its importance. I realize we shouldn’t edit it since it wasn’t created by us. There’s a question of whether we should inspect it, even though it might not be necessary. Then I shift to considering a method called `createProjection(Class<T>, Object)` from `ProxyProjectionFactory`. It's publicly inherited, even though the class itself is package-private. I'm pondering the ability to invoke public methods from an inaccessible superclass, and it seems that should work.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting MapAccessingMethodInterceptor**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I need to import `java.util.HashMap` for something native, but I think no, that’s probably not necessary. Then I wonder about Spring Data's `MapAccessingMethodInterceptor` and whether it returns Optional wrappers, but again, I think that’s not the case. So now, I want to take a closer look at the `MapAccessingMethodInterceptor` to check out its property names. There’s definitely something here worth clarifying!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ksURCuqowf2jUs7nL9dcD6JH|fc_02a82cff94ceadf8016a41c9cc4f088194866af8cae05b10f0", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge3/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.springframework.data/spring-data-commons/2.7.18/main/extracted/org/springframework/data/projection/MapAccessingMethodInterceptor.java", "limit": 220}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 281, "output": 347, "cacheRead": 23552, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24180, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782696386789, "responseId": "resp_02a82cff94ceadf8016a41c9c361748194a02316dccbdb3b79"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_ksURCuqowf2jUs7nL9dcD6